To the extent required by applicable law, whenever Pods Health collects personal information, Pods Health will:

\n •	provide timely and appropriate notice to you about our data practices;
\n •	collect your personal information only for specified and legitimate purposes. The information we collect will be relevant, adequate and not excessive for the purposes for which it is collected;
\n •	process your personal information in a manner consistent with the purposes for which it was originally collected or to which you have subsequently consented;
\n •	take commercially reasonable steps to ensure that your personal information is reliable for its intended use, accurate, complete, and, where necessary, kept up-to-date;
\n •	not use your personal information for direct marketing purposes without giving you an opportunity to “opt-out”; and
\n •	take appropriate measures, by contract or otherwise, to provide adequate protection for personal information that is disclosed to a third party or transferred to another country, including transfers within Pods Health.
